<div id="admin-tools" class="docs-section">
  <h2>Admin Tools</h2>
  <p>The following tools are available to system administrators.</p>

  <div class="docs-card">
    <h4>Manage Forms</h4>
    <p>Create, edit, and configure form templates. Set which fields appear, define approval workflows, and control form visibility in the sidebar.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="docs-card">
    <h4>ACL (Access Control Lists)</h4>
    <p>Manage groups and their members. Groups control access to admin tools, forms, and dashboard permissions. Add or remove employees from groups and configure group-level permissions.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="docs-card">
    <h4>Auth Console</h4>
    <p>Review and manage authorization records. Approve or deny access requests and audit the authorization history for employees.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="docs-card">
    <h4>Emulate</h4>
    <p>Temporarily log in as another employee to troubleshoot issues or verify their experience. An orange banner is displayed at the top of the page while emulating. Click <strong>Stop Emulating</strong> to return to your own session.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="docs-card">
    <h4>Billing Tools</h4>
    <p>Run monthly billing processes, move billing data between staging and production, and create backups. These operations interact with the billing stored procedures in GSABSS.</p>
  </div>
</div>
